Works very similarly to `useSignal()`, but it takes an object as its initial value and the reactivity extends to nested objects and arrays by default.
One can think of a store as a multiple-value signal or an object made of several signals.
Use `useStore(initialStateObject)` hook to create a reactive object.
It takes an initial object (or a factory function) and returns a reactive object.
